$ NastAero VM4: Cantilever Beam Modal Analysis (20 elements)
$ Reference: Euler-Bernoulli beam exact frequencies
$ L=1.0m, E=200GPa, A=0.01m^2, I=8.333e-6 m^4 (0.1m x 0.1m square)
$ rho=7850 kg/m^3
$
$ Analytical frequencies (cantilever):
$ f_n = (beta_n)^2/(2*pi*L^2) * sqrt(EI/(rho*A))
$ sqrt(EI/(rho*A)) = sqrt(200e9*8.333e-6/(7850*0.01)) = 1459.27 m/s
$
$ beta_1 = 1.8751, f1 = 3.516/(2*pi) * 1459.27/1.0 = 82.29 Hz (wait recalc)
$ Actually: f_n = beta_n^2 * sqrt(EI/(rho*A*L^4)) / (2*pi)
$ C = sqrt(EI/(rho*A)) = sqrt(200e9*8.333e-6/(7850*0.01)) = sqrt(2.126e8) = 14585.4
$ f1 = 1.8751^2 * C / (2*pi*L^2) = 3.5160 * 14585.4 / (6.2832*1.0) = 8163.6 Hz
$
$ Hmm let me use smaller I for more realistic frequencies:
$ Use 0.01m x 0.01m square: A=1e-4, I=8.333e-10
$ C = sqrt(200e9*8.333e-10/(7850*1e-4)) = sqrt(212739) = 461.24
$ f1 = 3.5160 * 461.24 / 6.2832 = 258.1 Hz  -- still high
$
$ Let's use L=10m to get reasonable frequencies:
$ f1 = 3.5160 * 461.24 / (6.2832*100) = 2.581 Hz
$
SOL 103
CEND
TITLE = VM4 - CANTILEVER BEAM MODES (20 ELEMENTS)
SPC = 1
METHOD = 1
